OL,3,CFrench woman recalls when British
OL,4,Ctroops liberated family on eve of D-Day
OL,6,FA woman whose family were the first
OL,7,FFrench people to be liberated by
OL,8,FBritish troops has spoken of that
OL,9,Fnight, as the
OL,11,FMadame Arlette Gondree was four years
OL,12,Fold when, on the night of 5 June 1944,
OL,13,Fa small unit of airborne troops,
OL,14,Flanded in France after setting off in
OL,15,Fwooden gliders from a base in Dorset.
OL,17,FThe mission of the troops from D
OL,18,FCompany of the Oxfordshire and
OL,19,FBuckinghamshire Light Infantry was to
OL,20,Ftake control of Pegasus Bridge, and
OL,21,Fanother, to slow the German's progress.
