OL,3,CFrench woman recalls when British
OL,4,Ctroops liberated family on eve of D-Day
OL,6,FOn the eve of D-Day, after the
OL,7,Fsoldiers had secured the bridge, they
OL,8,Fentered the Pegasus Bridge Cafe where
OL,9,Fa young Arlette and her family were
OL,10,Fhiding in the cellar.
OL,12,FArlette now runs the cafe and said:
OL,13,F"French children go to bed at a
OL,14,Fsimilar time to their parents so in
OL,15,FJune it is very late.
OL,17,F"It wasn't long before we were made
OL,18,Faware of a tremendous crashing noise
OL,19,Fand different voices around the house
OL,20,Fand different footsteps so we were
OL,21,Fvery frightened.
