OL,3,CFrench woman recalls when British
OL,4,Ctroops liberated family on eve of D-Day
OL,6,F"Daddy came into the room and ordered
OL,7,Fmy mother to take the two little girls
OL,8,Fdown into the cellar.
OL,10,F"Suddenly, we heard the window of our
OL,11,Fdining room being forced open and
OL,12,Ffootsteps above our heads, which was
OL,13,Fquite frightening. But Daddy left us
OL,14,Ffor a second - opened the door in the
OL,15,Fkitchen and was faced by two people
OL,16,Fwho said to him - it's OK, we've
OL,17,Farrived, we're British."
OL,19,FThe soldiers from D-Company were under
OL,20,Fthe commanded of Major John Howard.
