OL,3,CFrench woman recalls when British
OL,4,Ctroops liberated family on eve of D-Day
OL,6,FAfter entering the cafe, they had come
OL,7,Fbearing gifts that would temped
OL,8,FArlette out from hiding.
OL,10,F"They gave something that we had not
OL,11,Fhad for a long time. So, I came
OL,12,Fforward for the chocolate, of course.
OL,14,F"From that moment on, my parents said,
OL,15,F'What can we do for you?' So, we came
OL,16,Fup and the front door was open.
