OL,3,CFrench woman recalls when British
OL,4,Ctroops liberated family on eve of D-Day
OL,6,F"By then there were casualties and
OL,7,Fthey were brought in on the kitchen
OL,8,Ftable, in the dining room which was
OL,9,Fthe operating table and we were with
OL,10,Fthem the whole time because Mummy was
OL,11,Fa trained nurse."
OL,13,FArlette says her father was a great
OL,14,Flover of champagne and made sure that
OL,15,Fthe Germans would not get their hands
OL,16,Fon his supply.
