OL,3,CFrench woman recalls when British
OL,4,Ctroops liberated family on eve of D-Day
OL,6,F"He was determined the Germans were
OL,7,Fnot going to have it so they made a
OL,8,Fgreat big hole in the garden and
OL,9,Flowered in the champagne the wine and
OL,10,Fthe liquor and then they covered it
OL,11,Fwith corrugated iron and soil and grew
OL,12,Fvegetables on top.
OL,14,F"The Germans never found out about
OL,15,FDaddy's haul. But, when the British
OL,16,Farrived to give us the freedom and
OL,17,Fstarted digging their trenches in the
OL,18,Fgarden, Daddy said, 'It's all for you.
OL,19,FYou dig it up.'"
