OL,3,CFrench woman recalls when British
OL,4,Ctroops liberated family on eve of D-Day
OL,6,FOn the 80th anniversary of D-Day,
OL,7,FArlette will be hosting veterans at
OL,8,Fthe cafe to commemorate the specific
OL,9,Ftime at 11.16pm on 5 June when "Great
OL,10,FBritain brought us the freedom that we
OL,11,Fwere hoping for".
OL,13,FShe said: "We are very honoured to be
OL,14,Fthe first French family liberated.
OL,15,FThat is why they had a mission, but I
OL,16,Fhave one also."
